aScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/displayName\"><code>Function.prototype.displayName</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/length\"><code>Function.prototype.length</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/name\"><code>Function.prototype.name</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/prototype\"><code>Function.prototype.prototype</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li></ol></li><li><a href=\"#\"><strong>Methoden</strong></a><ol><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/apply\"><code>Function.prototype.apply()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/bind\"><code>Function.prototype.bind()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/call\"><code>Function.prototype.call()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/toString\"><code>Function.prototype.toString()</code></a></li></ol></li><li><strong><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object\"><code>Object</code></a></strong></li><li><a href=\"#\"><strong>Eigenschaften</strong></a><ol><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/constructor\"><code>Object.prototype.constructor</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/proto\"><code>Object.prototype.__proto__</code></a></li></ol></li><li><a href=\"#\"><strong>Methoden</strong></a><ol><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__defineGetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__defineGetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__defineSetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__defineSetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__lookupGetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__lookupGetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__lookupSetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__lookupSetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/hasOwnProperty\"><code>Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty()</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/isPrototypeOf\"><code>Object.prototype.isPrototypeOf()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/propertyIsEnumerable\"><code>Object.prototype.propertyIsEnumerable()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/setPrototypeOf\"><code>Object.setPrototypeOf()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toLocaleString\"><code>Object.prototype.toLocaleString()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toString\"><code>Object.prototype.toString()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/valueOf\"><code>Object.prototype.valueOf()</code></a></li></ol></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div id=\"sect1\"></div>\n\n<p>Die <strong><code>toString()</code></strong> Methode gibt einen string (Zeichenkette), die ein&nbsp;<a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number\"><code>Number</code></a> Objekt repräsentiert zurück.</p>\n\n<div id=\"sect2\"><iframe class=\"interactive\" height=\"490\" src=\"https://interactive-examples.mdn.mozilla.net/pages/js/number-tostring.html\" title=\"MDN Web Docs Interactive Example\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<pre class=\"syntaxbox notranslate\"><code><var>numObj</var>.toString([<var>radix</var>])</code></pre>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameter","title":"Parameter","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n <dt id=\"radix\"><code>radix</code></dt>\n <dd>Optional. Eine ganze Zahl im Bereich von 2 bis 36 welche die Basis des Zahlensystems angibt, in dem die Zahl repräsentiert werden soll.</dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"rückgabewert","title":"Rückgabewert","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Einen String, der das spezifizierte <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number\"><code>Number</code></a> Objekt&nbsp;repräsentiert.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"ausnahmen","title":"Ausnahmen","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n <dt id=\"rangeerror\"><a class=\"page-not-created\" title=\"Die Beschreibung hierüber wurde bisher noch nicht geschrieben. Bitte überlege, mitzuwirken!\"><code>RangeError</code></a></dt>\n <dd>Wenn <code>toString()</code> als <em>radix</em> Parameter eine Zahl kleiner 2 oder größer 36 übergeben bekommt, wird ein <a class=\"page-not-created\" title=\"Die Beschreibung hierüber wurde bisher noch nicht geschrieben. Bitte überlege, mitzuwirken!\"><code>RangeError</code></a> erzeugt.</dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"beschreibung","title":"Beschreibung","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Das <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number\"><code>Number</code></a> Objekt überschreibt die <code>toString()</code> Methode des <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object\"><code>Object</code></a> Objektes. Es erbt nicht von der&nbsp; <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toString\"><code>Object.prototype.toString()</code></a> Methode. Für <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number\"><code>Number</code></a> Objekte gibt die <code>toString()</code> Methode eine string-Repräsentation des Objektes in dem durch <em>radix</em> spezifizierten Zahlensystem zurück.</p>\n\n<p>Die <code>toString()</code> Methode analysiert das erste Argument und versucht eine string-Repräsentation im durch <em>radix</em> beschriebenen Zahlensystem zurück zu geben. Für <em>radix</em> (Basen) größer als 10 werden Buchstaben des Alphabets genutzt um Zahlen größer als 9 darzustellen. Zum Beispiel werden im Hexadezimalsystem (Basis 16) die Buchstaben <code>a</code> bis <code>f</code> eingesetzt.</p>\n\n<p>Wenn der <em>radix</em> Parameter nicht angegeben wird, wird 10, also das Dezimalsystem, angenommen.</p>\n\n<p>Wenn das <code>numObj</code> Objekt negativ&nbsp;ist, wird das Vorzeichen beibehalten. Dieses Verhalten ist auch im Binärsystem so: Der zurückgegebene string ist eine positive Binärdarstellung des <code>numObj</code> Objekts mit einem vorangestellten Minus (<code>-)</code> Zeichen. Es wird kein Zweierkomplement verwendet.</p>\n\n<p>Wenn das <code>numObj</code> Objekt keine ganze Zahl ist, wird ein Punkt (<code>.</code>) eingesetzt, um den ganzzahligen Teil von den Dezimalstellen zu trennen.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"beispiele","title":"Beispiele","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"einsatz_von_tostring","title":"Einsatz von <code>toString</code>","isH3":true,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> count <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>count<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">toString</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>    <span class=\"token comment\">// Ausgabe '10'</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">17</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">toString</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>     <span class=\"token comment\">// Ausgabe '17'</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">17.2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">toString</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>   <span class=\"token comment\">// Ausgabe '17.2'</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> x <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">6</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>x<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">toString</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>       <span class=\"token comment\">// Ausgabe '110'</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">254</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">toString</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">16</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  <span class=\"token comment\">// Ausgabe 'fe'</span>\n\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">toString</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>   <span class=\"token comment\">// Ausgabe '-1010'</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token number\">0xff</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">toString</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// Ausgabe '-11111111'</span>\n</code></pre></div>","titleAsText":"Einsatz von toString"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"spezifikationen","title":"Spezifikationen","isH3":false,"content":"<table class=\"standard-table\">\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Spezifikation</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Status</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Kommentar</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.ecma-international.org/publications/files/ECMA-ST-ARCH/ECMA-262,%201st%20edition,%20June%201997.pdf\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" title=\"Die 'ECMAScript 1st Edition (ECMA-262)' Spezifikation\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript 1st Edition (ECMA-262)</a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-standard\">Standard</span></td>\n   <td>Initiale Definition. Implementiert in JavaScript 1.1.</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.ecma-international.org/ecma-262/5.1/#sec-15.7.4.2\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript 5.1 (ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'Number.prototype.tostring' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-standard\">Standard</span></td>\n   <td>&nbsp;</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.ecma-international.org/ecma-262/6.0/#sec-number.prototype.tostring\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript 2015 (6th Edition, ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'Number.prototype.tostring' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-standard\">Standard</span></td>\n   <td>&nbsp;</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-number.prototype.tostring\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript (ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'Number.prototype.tostring' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-living\">Lebender Standard</span></td>\n   <td>&nbsp;</td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browserkompatibilität","id":"browserkompatibilität","isH3":false,"query":"javascript.builtins.Number.toString","dataURL":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/toString/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p></p><p></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"siehe_auch","title":"Siehe auch","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/toFixed\"><code>Number.prototype.toFixed()</code></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/toExponential\"><code>Number.prototype.toExponential()</code></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/toPrecision\"><code>Number.prototype.toPrecision()</code></a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Beschreibung","id":"beschreibung"},{"text":"Beispiele","id":"beispiele"},{"text":"Spezifikationen","id":"spezifikationen"},{"text":"Browserkompatibilität","id":"browserkompatibilität"},{"text":"Siehe auch","id":"siehe_auch"}],"summary":"Die toString() Methode gibt einen string (Zeichenkette), die ein Number Objekt repräsentiert zurück.","popularity":0.0005,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Number.prototype.toString()","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"Number.prototype.toString()","locale":"es","native":"Español"},{"title":"Number.prototype.toString()","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"Number.prototype.toString()","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"Number.prototype.toString()","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"},{"title":"Number.prototype.toString()","locale":"pl","native":"Polski"},{"title":"Number.prototype.toString()","locale":"pt-BR","native":"Português (do Brasil)"},{"title":"Number.prototype.toString()","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"Number.prototype.toString()","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"}],"source":{"folder":"de/web/javascript/reference/global_objects/number/tostring","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/files/de/web/javascript/reference/global_objects/number/tostring/index.html","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/commit/5fe4ab11259b37914fab41914e84897fea47d143","filename":"index.html"},"parents":[{"uri":"/de/docs/Web","title":"Webtechnologien für Entwickler"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript","title":"JavaScript"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference","title":"JavaScript-Referenz"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects","title":"Globale Objekte"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number","title":"Number"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/toString","title":"Number.prototype.toString()"}],"pageTitle":"Number.prototype.toString() - JavaScript | MDN","noIndexing":false}}